]]></contentSummary><contentType>website</contentType><subject>admission</subject><webLink xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[http://studieadres.nl]]></webLink></contentLink><contentLink><contentSummary xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[Theatre Studies in Amsterdam offers its students a broad range of possibilities to get insight into processes of theatrical creation and perception as well as aspects of theatricality in social life on international and national scale.]]></contentSummary><contentType>website</contentType><subject>objectives</subject><webLink xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[http://studieadres.nl]]></webLink></contentLink><contentLink><contentSummary xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[The Master's programme in Theatre Studies yields 60 ECTS credits: 42 credits of courses and a Thesis of 18 credits.]]></contentSummary><contentType>website</contentType><subject>curriculum</subject><webLink xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[http://studieadres.nl]]></webLink></contentLink><contentLink><contentSummary xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[Courses are offered as seminars in groups of 10 to 15 students.]]></contentSummary><contentType>website</contentType><subject>instruction modes</subject><webLink xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[http://studieadres.nl]]></webLink></contentLink><contentLink><contentSummary xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[Tuition fees are adjusted annually. For up-to-date information, please see www.uva.nl/isp]]></contentSummary><contentType>website</contentType><subject>tuition fee</subject><webLink xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[http://studieadres.nl]]></webLink></contentLink><contentLink><contentSummary xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[Graduates in Theatre Studies are qualified to pursue a career in diverse
areas, including theatre or theatre criticism, government institutions,
cultural organisations and international festival organisations. Research has
shown that most graduates find a job in their field of study within less than
a year. Many students already become closely associated with the theatre world during their studies, thus acquiring experience and connections that may help them later in finding a job.
]]></contentSummary><contentType>website</contentType><subject>job perspective</subject><webLink xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[http://studieadres.nl]]></webLink></contentLink><programDescription xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[Tekst, regie, acteurs, spel, kostuums, decor, belichting en geluid spelen allemaal een rol in een theatervoorstelling. Binnen de studie Theaterwetenschap bestudeer je als student de theorie en geschiedenis van teksten en voorstellingen, van spel, regie, vormgeving en van theaterbouw. Ook bestudeer je de rol van theater als maatschappelijk en cultureel fenomeen binnen onze samenleving. De master Theaterwetenschap geeft je de mogelijkheid je te specialiseren in die aspecten van theater die je interessant vindt.

De opleiding besteedt veel aandacht aan de ontwikkelingen van het theater in het Nederlandse taalgebied. In Amsterdam is het Theater Instituut Nederland gevestigd, evenals de Theaterschool. Beide instituten hebben een eigen bibliotheek, waar je als student Theaterwetenschap gebruik van kunt maken.

Er is ook een Engelstalige master Theatre Studies, een traject binnen de master Theaterwetenschap. Daarom zijn sommige onderdelen van de master in het Engels en volg je die onderdelen samen met internationale studenten. Zie onderstaande link voor meer informatie.]]></programDescription><programDescription xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[Aspects of theatre and performance are omnipresent in today's global community. It is therefore important to study theatre in the broadest sense of the word, not only as part of the national (Dutch) culture but also as a cultural phenomenon currently undergoing a process of globalisation. 

The Master's programme in Theatre Studies at the University of Amsterdam (UvA) provides a wide range of opportunities for acquiring insight into processes of theatrical creation and perception as well as aspects of theatricality both within and across cultures. The courses are organised around four themes: theatre and history, theatre and society, performance and theatre analysis, theories of theatre, performance and performativity.]]></programDescription><programName xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[Arts and Culture: Theatre Studies]]></programName><programName xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[Arts and Culture: Theatre Studies]]></programName><programSummary xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[Theaterwetenschap beslaat een breed vakgebied. Aan de Universiteit van Amsterdam richt de opleiding zich vooral op het onderzoek naar theater in Europa en de Verenigde Staten.]]></programSummary><programSummary xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[The Master's programme in Theatre Studies at the University of Amsterdam (UvA) provides opportunities to acquire insight into the processes of theatrical creation and perception. ]]></programSummary><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[theater]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[toneel]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[beeldende kunst]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[cultuur]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[dramaturgie]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[film]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[kunst]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[kunstacademie]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[literatuur]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[theatre]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[drama]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[visual arts]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[culture]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[dramaturgy]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[movie]]></searchword><searchw